sugar through hole in mixing bowl lid, ensuring the first tablespoon of sugar is fully incorporated before adding the next. Set aside half of the egg white mixture."},{"content":"Add chocolate custard to egg white mixture in mixing bowl and combine <b>4 sec\/\/speed 2<b> until just combined. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add reserved egg white mixture and combine <b>4 sec\/\/speed 2<b> until just combined. Mixture should be light and fluffy. Divide mixture between prepared ramekins. Smooth over tops and wipe around ramekin rims with a clean kitchen towel."},{"content":"Place ramekins onto preheated baking tray. Bake for 25-30 minutes (180°C), or until soufflés have risen approx. 3 cm above the rim and are lightly golden on top. Remove from oven and dust with icing sugar. Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This soufflé is slightly denser in consistency than a traditional soufflé, similar in texture to a baked custard. The rise while baking provides a lovely mousse like texture to the end result.","Custard will keep in a sealable container for a couple of days in the refrigerator."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","55m","2 portions"]}